The paper discusses the use of cryptographic and encryption techniques for message authentication in wireless sensor networks, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR) and network security (cs.NI). The paper also considers the limited resources of WSNs, which suggests a focus on software engineering (cs.SE) and algorithms (cs.DS) to optimize the techniques used. Finally, the paper discusses the cost and feasibility of the techniques, which could fall under the category of cyber economics (cs.CY).
